# Look Forward Model — AI Pricing Simulator
**TELUS · Senior AI Product Manager · Mobility Pricing Portfolio · 2024 – Present**

---

## The problem

TELUS pricing analysts were spending 3 hours per scenario to manually model the financial and volume impact of potential pricing decisions using Excel. The process was slow, inconsistent, and bottlenecked the team's ability to respond to market moves in real time.

The deeper issue: pricing decisions at a national telecom involve enormous financial stakes. When a competitor moves on pricing and it takes your team 3 hours to model a response — or worse, when the model is only as good as whoever built it that day — the business is flying partially blind. The pricing team needed a co-pilot, not another spreadsheet.

---

## My role

I was the Product Manager for the Mobility Pricing Portfolio, responsible for defining, building, and shipping the Look Forward Model as the flagship product of a broader pricing intelligence suite.

I owned: problem framing, technical requirements, model architecture decisions, stakeholder alignment, go-live strategy, and ongoing adoption.

