## What I built

The Look Forward Model is an AI-driven simulator that allows pricing analysts to generate volume and financial impact forecasts for pricing scenarios in approximately 20 minutes — an 85%+ reduction in time-to-insight.

**Core models:**

| Model | What it predicts | Accuracy achieved |
|---|---|---|
| Renewal Model (HUP Finance) | Device-plan renewal volumes | 86.3% R-squared, 17.7% MAPE |
| Activation Model (BYOP & Finance) | New plan activations | 81.7% R-squared, 20% MAPE |
| Deactivation/Churn Model | Phase 1 data structuring complete | In development |

All MVP models exceeded the 70% R-squared target and the <30% MAPE target during testing.

**Modeling approach:**

I selected and oversaw a hierarchical linear modeling approach (mixed modeling) that accounts for both fixed effects (general market trends) and random effects (segment-level variations). This was not the default choice — it was the right choice for the granularity we needed.

**Model granularity:** Channel → Pricing Region (ROC, QC) → Plan Group (5G, 5G+ US/MEX) → Device Group/Generation. This level of specificity was a deliberate design decision I pushed for, because national-level averages were masking the segment-level dynamics that actually drove revenue.

**Key inputs and levers the model supports:**
- Pricing levers: Finance Floor, STIM amount, Bill Credit amount
- Dynamic features: seasonality, competitive pricing (from real-time trackers), account attributes (age, number of lines), online clickstream data (renewal page visits)

