## Strategic decisions I made

**The "Three-Way Synergy" framework:** I established the Look Forward Model as part of an integrated three-product ecosystem — Look Back (historical intelligence) → Look Forward (predictive) → Market Mix Model (long-term simulation). This wasn't technically required for the first product, but it was the right architectural decision because it gave us a portfolio rather than a one-off tool. Each product feeds the next.

**Tiered pricing experimentation:** I developed a methodology to categorize cities into three tiers based on pricing sensitivity. This allowed TELUS to match competitor prices in high-sensitivity Tier 1 cities while protecting profit margins in Tier 2 and 3 regions — hyper-local experimentation at national scale.

**Black Friday impact quantification:** The model revealed that approximately 21% of Black Friday renewal volume was driven by the holiday effect itself, independent of promotional credits or device STIM. This was a non-obvious insight that directly informed promotional investment decisions.

---

## Key insights delivered

The model proved that **device promotions (STIM and BiB) drive significantly higher volume impact compared to simple rate changes**. This finding shifted how the pricing team prioritized promotional levers — a strategic shift made possible only because we had a model rigorous enough to isolate the variables.

