## Adoption and integration

I developed the training roadmap and handbook for three user types: base team, planning analysts, and pricing primes. The transition from Excel to the AI tool was seamless because adoption was treated as a product problem, not a training problem.

**Project Janus integration:** I led the mapping of 49–50 critical data points between the Janus Data Modernization Project and the Look Forward Model, including 27 plan-related and 15 device-related data points in the TOM API. This was unglamorous but essential — a model is only as good as its data foundation.

